<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="159" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,1084,1288]" pageId="8" pageNumber="159">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1119,1144]" pageId="8" pageNumber="159">Comments.</emphasis>
A single specimen was collected in a shaded mountain stream above 
<quantity box="[1138,1197,1119,1144]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.6" pageId="8" pageNumber="159" unit="m" value="66.0">66 m</quantity>
asl, with clear water and a stony bottom. The first record for 
<collectingCountry box="[637,720,1156,1181]" name="Tunisia" pageId="8" pageNumber="159">Tunisia</collectingCountry>
is from 
<bibRefCitation author="Lambertie" box="[828,1029,1156,1181]" pageId="8" pageNumber="159" refString="Lambertie, M. (1907) Notules hemipterologiques. Hemipteres recueillis en Tunisie par M. Blanc. Proces-Verbaux de la Societe linneenne de Bordeaux, 62 (1907 - 8), 25 - 27." type="journal article" year="1907">
Lambertie (
<number box="[963,1021,1156,1180]" pageId="8" pageNumber="159" value="1907.0">1907</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
in northern 
<collectingCountry box="[1181,1264,1156,1181]" name="Tunisia" pageId="8" pageNumber="159">Tunisia</collectingCountry>
(Aïn Draham, Jendouba).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="159" type="distribution">
